<br>
Would any of you, being a Mage, of lvl 51 and above, be willing to go on a Staff-of-mastery gathering type raid?<br>
<br>
A mage-only deal I think would be wonderful - I'm sure we all have Cleric friends if a CR is in order... <br>
and poer group of 4 mages a Cleric and Enchanter too.<br>
<br>
I think that 4 pets of different forms make a great team...<br>
An earth to root, an air to stun, a fire to nuke and a water to freeze...  the chanter to give manaboost, do crowd-control if need be and enchance our pets with buffs... the cleric - heal the caster that gets hit upon by accident, also buff pets etc...<br>
<br>
Sounds to me like the mob wouldni stand a chance...  Maybe even throw in an EPIC pet (anyone that has them).<br>
<br>
And since the pets keep the mob busy, we can DoT and sit and med, nuke, sit and med, chain-cast pets if need be, ...  <br>
After all, pets are expendable (even though I love my Jobaners and Kartiks and such).<br>
<br>
I think one other server has arranged a raiding of sorts, and I for one would think it a bold thing to try, but an intresting one nevertheless.<br>
<br>
Since with the PoP-expansion, raids can be more easily managed, we can have 4 mages a group, a chanter and a cleric.... and then a few of those groups?<br>
<br>
What do you think?  Feel like giving it a shot?<br>
Also - we would need a capable leader - so, anyone up for organising this, please... pretty please?<br>
<br>
Yanari Pethugger,<br>
Gnome, Mage.<br>
